      <p>
       The Student Mentoring and Research Teams (SMART) program is planned to be integrated with the Discovery Experience that is part of the the campus Strategic Plan. It will not be offered as a separate program this year. In the meantime, we will continue to offer
       <a href="https://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2019-spring-gspdp-301-001-sem-001" rel="noopener" target="_blank">
        GSPDP 301: Mentoring in Higher Education
       </a>
       in Spring 2019. We strongly encourage graduate students who have an interest in mentoring undergraduates in research to take the class.
      </p>
      <div class="row">
       <div class="col-md-6 homelink">
        <h2>
         What is SMART?
        </h2>
        <p>
         Student Mentoring and Research Teams (SMART) is a program that enables doctoral students to create mentored research opportunities for undergraduate students at UC Berkeley. The program provides summer funding for both graduate and undergraduate participants and opportunities to share research results on campus and at national conferences.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="/graduate" title="Graduate Applicants">
          Graduate Applicants
         </a>
         |
         <a href="/undergraduate" title="Undergraduate Applicants">
          Undergraduate Applicants
         </a>
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="col-md-6 homelink">
        <h2>
         Why Support SMART?
        </h2>
        <p>
         Gifts to the SMART program are more than matched by University contributions. Each team’s sponsorship provides stipends of up to $5,000 to graduate mentors and $3,500 to undergraduate mentees. Up to $1,000 may also be made available to SMART mentors for travel or research expenses that cannot be covered elsewhere.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a href="http://smart.berkeley.edu/support-smart/" title="More Information">
          Learn More
         </a>
         |
         <a href="http://smart.berkeley.edu/media/2018-smart-teams.pdf">
          Meet the 2018 Teams
         </a>
         |
         <a href="https://givetocal.berkeley.edu/egiving/index.cfm?Fund=FU1050000" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Make a Gift Online">
          Make a Gift Online
         </a>
        </p>
